@mike-north as far as I can tell `import { htmlSafe } from '@ember/string';` still works and is not deprecated. However official [docs](http://api.emberjs.com/ember/3.13/functions/@ember%2Ftemplate/htmlSafe) say to import from `@ember/template`.

I imagine that the import from `@ember/string` should/will be deprecated at some point.

When I used `@deprecated` here I was thinking that I was deprecating the dts import itself. I'm happy to remove `@deprecated` to revisit at a later date since there is no underlying deprecation to match.

